Document: AudioStreamPlayer
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamplayer.rst
Summary: This section details the methods, signals, and the MixTarget enumeration for the AudioStreamPlayer class.

Methods:
*   get_playback_position() → float
*   get_stream_playback() → AudioStreamPlayback
*   has_stream_playback() → bool
*   play(from_position: float = 0.0) → void
*   seek(to_position: float) → void
*   stop() → void

Signals:
*   finished(): Emitted when a sound finishes playing without interruptions. This signal is not emitted when calling stop(), or when exiting the tree while sounds are playing.

Enumerations:
enum MixTarget:
*   MIX_TARGET_STEREO = 0: The audio will be played only on the first channel. This is the default.
*   MIX_TARGET_SURROUND = 1: The audio will be played on all surround channels.
*   MIX_TARGET_CENTER = 2: The audio will be played on the second channel, which is usually the center.
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioStreamPlayer
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamplayer.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring an AudioStreamPlayer node, including playback control, audio routing, and sound characteristics.

Property Descriptions:

*   **autoplay** (bool)
    Default: `false`
    Description: If `true`, this node calls play() when entering the tree.
    Set/Get methods: set_autoplay(value: bool), is_autoplay_enabled()

*   **bus** (StringName)
    Default: `"Master"`
    Description: The target bus name. All sounds from this node will be playing on this bus.
    Note: At runtime, if no bus with the given name exists, all sounds will fall back on "Master". See also AudioServer.get_bus_name().
    Set/Get methods: set_bus(value: StringName), get_bus()

*   **max_polyphony** (int)
    Default: `1`
    Description: The maximum number of sounds this node can play at the same time. Calling play() after this value is reached will cut off the oldest sounds.
    Set/Get methods: set_max_polyphony(value: int), get_max_polyphony()

*   **mix_target** (MixTarget)
    Default: `0`
    Description: The mix target channels. Has no effect when two speakers or less are detected (see SpeakerMode).
    Set/Get methods: set_mix_target(value: MixTarget), get_mix_target()

*   **pitch_scale** (float)
    Default: `1.0`
    Description: The audio's pitch and tempo, as a multiplier of the stream's sample rate. A value of `2.0` doubles the audio's pitch, while a value of `0.5` halves the pitch.
    Set/Get methods: set_pitch_scale(value: float), get_pitch_scale()

*   **playback_type** (PlaybackType)
    Default: `0`
    Description: Experimental: This property may be changed or removed in future versions. The playback type of the stream player. If set other than to the default value, it will force that playback type.
    Set/Get methods: set_playback_type(value: PlaybackType), get_playback_type()

*   **playing** (bool)
    Default: `false`
    Description: If `true`, this node is playing sounds. Setting this property has the same effect as play() and stop().
    Set/Get methods: set_playing(value: bool), is_playing()

*   **stream** (AudioStream)
    Description: The AudioStream resource to be played. Setting this property stops all currently playing sounds. If left empty, the AudioStreamPlayer does not work.
    Set/Get methods: set_stream(value: AudioStream), get_stream()

*   **stream_paused** (bool)
    Default: `false`
    Description: If `true`, the sounds are paused. Setting stream_paused to `false` resumes all sounds.
    Note: This property is automatically changed when exiting or entering the tree, or this node is paused (see Node.process_mode).
    Set/Get methods: set_stream_paused(value: bool), get_stream_paused()

*   **volume_db** (float)
    Default: `0.0`
    Description: Volume of sound, in decibels. This is an offset of the stream's volume.
    Note: To convert between decibel and linear energy (like most volume sliders do), use volume_linear, or @GlobalScope.db_to_linear() and @GlobalScope.linear_to_db().
    Set/Get methods: set_volume_db(value: float), get_volume_db()

*   **volume_linear** (float)
    Description: Volume of sound, as a linear value.
    Note: This member modifies volume_db for convenience. The returned value is equivalent to the result of @GlobalScope.db_to_linear() on volume_db. Setting this member is equivalent to setting volume_db to the result of @GlobalScope.linear_to_db() on a value.
    Set/Get methods: set_volume_linear(value: float), get_volume_linear()
